Study method: Pomodoro
  Using the Pomodoro method, you break your workday into 25-minute focus periods followed by five-minute breaks.
  Each of these focus periods plus a break period is called a Pomodoroâ€”after the tomato-shaped timer first used to test the method.
  
Tips to improve memory:
  1. Get enough sleep: 8-10 hours through the night.
  2. Exercise regularly - aerobic exercises
  3. Mindfulness: meditation and a calm brain
  4. Engage in brain boosting activity that is challenging
  5. Practice retrieval: recalling facts without using Google (e.g. trivia)
